The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | World Bank loan hope 
                                                                                                               World Bank loan hope 
                            
	New Delhi, March 20 (PTI): India Infrastructure Finance Company Ltd (IIFCL) said the World Bank would disburse a loan of $1.2 billion next month for its infrastructure projects.        
	We have been told yesterday, that they (World Bank) are disbursing it in the April meeting, IIFCL chairman S.S. Kohli said on the sidelines of a Ficci summit.         
	IIFCL has also signed an agreement with the Asian Development Bank for a $200-million loan.        
	The company has raised Rs 2,600 crore till March 17 from the second tranche of its Rs 10,000-crore tax-free bonds programme.         
	From the first tranche, IIFCL had raised Rs 7,370 crore in the third week of January.         
	The bonds, guaranteed by the government, will give a 6.85 per cent tax-free return and have a maturity period of five years. The funds are for refinancing infrastructure projects, particularly highways and ports. The government allowed the company to raise funds through the tax-free bonds in December.                                                                                                                                        
